                    <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb/>
                    <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> שר דפנא <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>[That which] offered q‘/l[...<lb/>...] governor of Daphna [...</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>The editors suggested אח]שדרפנא "satrap, the ruler of a Persian province", as
                    alternative reading for the second line. Both the picture and the drawing of the
                    fragment do not seem to support this interpretation. Moreover, as they
                    themselves note in the commentary, the presence of such a title in an
                    inscription from the Hellenistic period would be puzzling.</p>
            </div>
